  fishName: Banggus
  scientificName: Chanos chanos
  description: Also known as Milkfish. While not globally endangered, wild populations
    in the Philippines face threats from habitat loss and overfishing.
  status: 0
  iucnStatus: Vulnerable (wild populations)
  populationTrend: Decreasing (wild populations)
  habitat: Coastal waters, lagoons, and estuaries. Spawns in open sea, juveniles
    migrate to shallow waters
  distribution: Indo-Pacific region, particularly important in Philippines, Indonesia,
    and Taiwan
  threats: Habitat destruction of spawning grounds, coastal development, pollution,
    overfishing of wild stocks, climate change
  importance: National fish of the Philippines, culturally and economically significant,
    important food source, supports aquaculture industry
  conservationEfforts: Marine protected areas for spawning grounds, sustainable fishing
    practices, aquaculture to reduce wild catch pressure, habitat protection
